Yesterday we had a slightly scary moment when one of our robots “departed control” (video), which made me remember the topic of tuning the failsafes. The 2025 DS is supposed to include a different tuning (looser?) than 2024, which itself is different (stricter?) than 2023.

In this instance, the robot started ignoring the DS at around the same time that the battery voltage was getting close to the brown-out limit – our setpoint generator prevents the RoboRIO brownout control from ever being triggered; instead, the robot just slows down, as you can see in the video.

Anybody else experience this sort of thing this year?

For folks working on the end-to-end safety heartbeat (if you’re listening on CD? :- ), FYI.
